<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - REMOVE AND
        INSTALL - SPLASH PANELS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SPLASH PANELS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The splash panels (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900618">Figure 18</hotlnk>) on the 8500 series minimizes splash and mud, protecting
                vital engine systems from corrosion and malfunction.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel Removal: Passenger Side</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Figure 19</hotlnk>
                for items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the attachment bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Item 6</hotlnk>) at the forward lower section of the splash guard mounting
                    bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Item 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the rear splash panel mounting bracket (passenger side shown) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Item 2</hotlnk>) . Remove the mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>) from the mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900618" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900618.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Splash Panel -Passenger Side Shown</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL - PASSENGER SIDE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUMPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT AND CLEARANCE LIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. CHASSIS FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel Removal: Drivers Side</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood tilted locate the driver side 2 forward mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900620">Item 2, Figure 20</hotlnk>) attaching the splash panel to the front hood
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts and lock washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 rear splash panel mounting bolts and lock washers located along the upper
                    edge of the splash panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900619" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900619.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Splash Panel Removal (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRAME RAIL SPLASH PANEL BRACKET MOUNTING POINTS, REAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FRAME RAIL SPLASH PANEL BRACKET MOUNTING POINTS, FRONT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. FRONT SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. HOOD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel Install</title>
            <para>Beginning on the passenger side:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the splash panel mounting holes with the mounting brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900619">Item 6, Figure 19</hotlnk>) and insert the mounting bolts and lock
                    washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hand tighten only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the splash panel rear mounting holes with the mounting holes in the bracket
                    assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900618">Items 1 and 3, Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the mounting bolts and lock washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the splash panel mounting bolts to 46 - 51 Nm (34 - 38 lbf-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900620" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900620.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Splash Panel Install (Drivers Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOOD TILTED UPPER DRIVERS SIDE SECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TWO UPPER SPLASH SHIELD MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the hood/fender splash panel on the inner fender of the hood/fender assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900620">Item 2, Figure 20</hotlnk>) . Install the 2 forward mounting bolts and
                    lock washer to the hood/fender assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the 2 rear splash panel mounting holes in place on the hood and install the
                    mounting bolts and lock washers, securing it to the hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to 46 - 51 Nm (34 - 38 lbf-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close hood and lock hood latches.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
